780
00:54:11,241 --> 00:54:13,120
Rym: Yeah, I'm so much better than everyone else who can't hear it.

781
00:54:13,160 --> 00:54:15,424
Scott: When in fact, it might not even be a gold cable.

782
00:54:15,464 --> 00:54:25,420
Scott: It's probably just like a cable spray-painted with gold, and, you know, with some lead in it to make it heavy, and it doesn't make the sound any better than the cheap-ass cables from RadioShack.

783
00:54:25,460 --> 00:54:36,880
Rym: That's actually one trick that a lot of low-end but marketed to the high-end audience will use, is they will put weights inside of their equipment to make it feel heavier and feel more massive and meaningful.

784
00:54:37,140 --> 00:54:51,460
Scott: Yes, if you want to buy a stereo, right, and you're not sure if it's going to sound good or not, or if you're spending too much to make it sound good, all you have to do is pay attention to one, the speakers, and two, the amplifier.

785
00:54:51,860 --> 00:54:59,353
Rym: The best thing to do is just run some sort of blind test where you get someone else to play the two stereos while you stand with your back turned, and see if you can hear the difference.

786
00:54:59,393 --> 00:54:59,854
Rym: And you know what?

787
00:55:00,355 --> 00:55:03,060
Rym: If you can't easily tell the difference, there's effectively no difference.

788
00:55:03,220 --> 00:55:04,540
Scott: And you just buy whichever one's cheaper.

789
00:55:05,381 --> 00:55:16,340
